    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix off-by-one error in UL reference signal generation\n\n### Summary\nThe UL reference signal generation code in `lte_ul_ref.c` contained two off-by-one errors that could lead to buffer overreads and incorrect memory deallocation. \n\nIn `generate_ul_ref_sigs_rx()`, the debug print statement was using `n<<2` as an array index, which would access memory beyond the allocated buffer size. The allocated buffer has `2*dftsizes[Msc_RS]` elements, but the print statement was attempting to access up to `4*dftsizes[Msc_RS]` elements.\n\nAdditionally, in `free_ul_ref_sigs()`, the deallocation size was incorrectly specified as `4*sizeof(int16_t)*dftsizes[Msc_RS]` instead of the correct `2*sizeof(int16_t)*dftsizes[Msc_RS]`, causing a mismatch between allocation and deallocation sizes.\n\nThese issues could be triggered when the UE processes uplink reference signals, potentially leading to segmentation faults or memory corruption during PHY initialization.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_REFSIG/lte_ul_ref.c`: \n  - Fixed array indexing in debug print statement in `generate_ul_ref_sigs_rx()` (line 170)\n  - Corrected memory deallocation size in `free_ul_ref_sigs()` (line 219)\n\n"
}